title: For Sale:  Borchardt C-93 (AH3377) FOR SALE.
postcontent: Borchardt C-93 Automatic Pistol. Made by Ludwig Lowe in 1893. This gun is in mint condition as professionally restored. It comes with the original stock and holster which are in original condition. This gun is virtually undetectable as being a restoration as the restoration is next to perfect. These 1893 Borchardt pistols were the true forerunner of the world famous and historic Luger pistol. The Luger employed the unique toggling breech mechanism which was eventually adopted and refined by George Luger and was used throughout production of the Luger pistol. A truly great rare gun in near mint condition!

U.S.M.C. logo and inscription have been laser engraved in the rear of the stock. Cleaning kit is brand new and never been installed in the gun. The scope mount is a Gen 4 Springfield Aluminum mount that is also brand new never installed. This gun has had the bolt locking lugs professionally lapped to the receiver to ensure full bearing on both lugs. This is a process of lapping the lugs while spring pressure dives the bolt back, and ensuring proper headspace is maintained. Bolt will close on a 1.6 go-gauge, several thousandths shy of closing on a 1.64 no-go-gauge, and clearly far from closing on a Field-gauge. The lapping ensures safety and precision as the bolt locking lugs fully share the bolt thrust during the firing cycle. The amount of headspace is about 1.63 which puts this at a chamber dimension consistent with that used by the military. It is not excessively tight, but will chamber either NATO 7.62X51 or .308 Win. without overpressure or carbon build up causing clearance issues. This is a very shootable gun. I have sighted it in per the military field manual for M80 147 gr. ball ammo. Elevation adjustments are dead on, I have shot it out as far as 500 yards open sight with precision you would expect from this gun. Also included will be the manuals, the lock, the padded travel case, the military standard marksman sling, 2 original 10 round magazines from Springfield Armory, as well as the scope mount with Leupold rings, and the cleaning kit. Overall this is a very unique, field ready rifle that is in pristine enough condition for a display piece.

title: For Sale:  Waffen Werks AK-74 5.45X39
postcontent:
The AK-74 shoots a 5.45x39mm round. The mechanics of the AK-74 work exactly as the reliable AK-47. You get the same function, reliability but a reduced recoil when firing the smaller round.

title: For Sale:  NEW LWRC International M6A2 5.56 LWRC 14.7" FDE (M6A2R5FDE14.7)
postcontent:
**WHILE SUPPLIES LAST**

The M6A2 rifle is a standard carbine available in various barrel lengths and in either 5.56mm NATO or 6.8mm SPC. The M6A2 rifle is ideal for those who utilize optical sights as it employs a low- profile gas block. There is no A-frame front sight to obscure the field of view of the optical device. The M6A2 rifle also features a longer midlength free float rail system with a removable return-to-zero top. Any M4 MIL Std 1913 accessory can be mounted to the rail, and because the rail has a monolithic profile, you can bridge devices from the receiver to the rail seamlessly. The longer rail also affords more 1913 real estate to mount your accessories.

The M6A2 rifle can be used in various roles. With the 10.5 inch barrel, it is ideal for close quarters battle or fighting in built up areas. The 14.7 inch barrel M6A2 rifle is an excellent general purpose carbine capable of effective fire out to 600 meters. And with the 16.1 inch barrel, the M6A2 rifle can be used as a Squad Dedicated Marksman Rifle.

The M6A2 rifles edge in capability, reliability, accuracy and long service life is the result of advanced technology materials and manufacturing processes, combined with progressive patented designs. All LWRCI carbine systems feature our short-stroke gas-piston operating system. The operating system is lightweight, self-regulating, and self-scraping. This system of operation does not foul the moving parts of the weapon with carbon or heat, greatly enhancing service life and reliability while decreasing both user and armorer maintenance. All M6A2 rifles feature a match grade, cold rotary hammer forged barrel with a target crown. The barrel is treated with NiCorr surface conversion technology that extends service life, enhances accuracy, and increases the effective range of the weapon. As in all of our rifles, the bolt carrier group and the barrel extension of the M6A2 rifle is coated with EXOs patented nickel-boron surface conversion technology that provides a hard permanent lubrication to the moving parts.

The M6A2 rifle defines itself as the most modern and incrementally evolved carbine in the world. At the same time it also presents the best value. Service life is extended to four times that of a legacy M4, accuracy is 100 percent better, and our M6 rifles are many times more reliable than the legacy gas-impingement design.

postcontent:
An 80% lower receiver is a partially completed piece of metal that requires special tooling and skills to be completed, a trigger assembly, and a complete upper to be considered a firearm. Unlike a stripped receiver it is not required to be transferred through a Federal Firearms Licensed holder (FFL).
These are high quality 80% lowers made from 7075 t6 aircraft grade aluminium with fully broached magazine wells for perfect dropping al ALL magazines. They are made to 100% military specifications and will work with any Mil Spec Jig although I recommend the ones made for these lowers cause they work very well and come with all of the drill bits need to complete the job as well as detailed instructions. They come with a bead-blasted raw aluminium finish that looks very good as-is or is ready for paint. These are the ONLY 80% receivers on the market that have been given permission by the ATF to have the rear pocket area that the rear take-down inserts into already milled out for you. One of the most troublesome areas to drill out and its already done for you. Now you don't have to worry about the rear take-down pin detent bore being ruined as it is all perfectly milled to spec.
